gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Knicks 114, Lakers 109
gameRecap.excerpt: The Knicks defeated the Lakers, 114-109. Jalen Brunson led the way for the Knicks with 29 points (3-6 3pt FG), four rebounds and three assists, while Julius Randle added 27 points and 14 rebounds in the victory. LeBron James tallied 25 points, 10 rebounds and 11 assists for the Lakers in the losing effort, his 2nd triple-double of the season, and 109th of his career. The Knicks improve to 15-11 on the season, while the Lakers fall to 15-12.
